cgroups:
        cgroups are used to limit the resources. So, that no process can eat the entire cgroups


namespace:
        namespace is used for isolation
    types:
        PID:
            Process ID namespace is used to bring the isolation between the process id that each container has its own unique process id sequence.
        Mount:
            Mount namespace is used to isolate the filesystem mount points
            that each container has its root filesystem and cannot see the host root unless it is mounted
        Network:
            Network namespace isolates the network interfaces, IP address, ports and each container has its own IP address, routing table, virtual network interface.
        UTS:
            unix time sharing system namespace isolates the host name and domain name. So each container has its own host name.
        IPC:
            Inter process communication namespace isolates the shared memory, message queue, semaphores. So even if two containers are sharing 
            the same resources they can't communicate with each other.
        User:
            User namespace is to isolate the user IDs and group IDs. 
